Q: $ABCDEFGH$ shown below is a right rectangular prism.  If the volume of pyramid $ABCH$ is 20, then what is the volume of $ABCDEFGH$?

[asy]

import three;

triple A,B,C,D,EE,F,G,H;

A = (0,0,0);

B = (5,0,0);

C = (5,6,0);

D= (0,6,0);

EE = (0,0,4);

F = B+EE;

G = C + EE;

H = D + EE;

draw(B--C--D);

draw(B--A--D,dashed);

draw(EE--F--G--H--EE);

draw(A--EE,dashed);

draw(B--F);

draw(C--G);

draw(D--H);

label("$A$",A,S);

label("$B$",B,W);

label("$C$",C,S);

label("$D$",D,E);

label("$E$",EE,N);

label("$F$",F,W);

label("$G$",G,SW);

label("$H$",H,E);

[/asy]

solution:
We add the edges of the pyramid to our diagram below.

[asy]
import three;
triple A,B,C,D,EE,F,G,H;
A = (0,0,0);
B = (5,0,0);
C = (5,6,0);
D= (0,6,0);
EE = (0,0,4);
F = B+EE;
G = C + EE;
H = D + EE;
draw(B--C--D);
draw(B--A--D,dashed);
draw(EE--F--G--H--EE);
draw(B--H--A--EE,dashed);
draw(A--C,dashed);
draw(B--F);
draw(C--G);
draw(D--H--C);
label("$A$",A,SSW);
label("$B$",B,W);
label("$C$",C,S);
label("$D$",D,E);
label("$E$",EE,N);
label("$F$",F,W);
label("$G$",G,SW);
label("$H$",H,E);
[/asy]

Taking $ABC$ to be the base of pyramid $ABCH$, the height is $HD$.  Therefore, the volume of pyramid $ABCH$ is $$\frac{[ABC](HD)}{3}.$$We are given that this volume equals 20, so we have \[{[ABC]\cdot HD}=60.\]The volume of prism $ABCDEFGH$ is the product of area of $ABCD$ and the height of the prism, which equals $HD$.   The area of $ABC$ is half the area of rectangle $ABCD$, so we have  \begin{align*}
\text{Volume of }ABCDEFGH &= ([ABCD])(HD) \\
&= 2([ABC])(HD) \\
&= \boxed{120}.\end{align*}

